parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Booster Line Check Valve Freeze
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster line check valve can cause the brakes to become hard to press, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard to press
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to slow down or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The warping of the brake rotors can cause the vehicle to experience extended stopping distances, vibration, and shaking, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal pulsates
the steering wheel shakes
the vehicle vibrates when braking
the brake rotors are excessively worn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration and braking can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward
the brake pedal is hard to press
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Line Leaks and Gasoline Odor in Passenger Compartment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel line leaks can cause a strong smell of gasoline in the passenger compartment, which can lead to health hazards, nausea, headaches, and potentially even fires.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline in the passenger compartment
especially in cold weather
fuel vapors
nausea
headaches.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
loss of control
accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch shudder/chatter can cause hesitation during acceleration, making it difficult to merge onto traffic or accelerate quickly, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Clutch shudders or chatters when engaged
hesitation during acceleration
car jerks or trembles when shifting into gear
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or loses power
transmission slips or hesitates
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission
difficulty shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Park mechanism failure can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly when in park
park mechanism does not engage properly
vehicle does not stay in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the rear subframe can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as it can lead to the separation of the rear suspension and affect the vehicle's stability.
symptoms: The rear subframe is severely corroded
the rear subframe is fractured
the rear tire is bent inward
the vehicle is difficult to control
the vehicle spins out of control
the vehicle crashes into an embankment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction and vibration of the steering column can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as it can affect the vehicle's stability and make it difficult to steer.
symptoms: The steering wheel vibrates violently
the vehicle vibrates when turning the steering wheel
the steering wheel jerks out of the driver's hand
the vehicle goes to the right while driving.
